#Codebook 

The file run_analysis.R contains the code that executes the data preparation and do the 5 transformations required for the final peer-reviewed project of the "Getting and Cleaning Data". The code executes the following steps:

1. Download the file and save it locately. 
2. Read data from the targeting files. 
3. Merges the training and the test sets to create one data set.
4. Extracts only the measurements on the mean and standard deviation for each measurement.
5. Uses descriptive activity names from "activity_labels.txt" to name the activities in the data set. 
6. Appropriately labels the data set with descriptive variable names.
7. Creates a independent tidy data set with the average of each variable for each activity and each subject and saved it as a .txt file named "tidydata.txt". 

Done. 
